{{.Out.backup}}

Write 'restore.sh', a matching bash script that takes such a 'backup-*.tar.gz' archive as its first argument and a target directory as its optional second argument (defaulting to the current directory), then extracts the archive into the target. It must start with '#!/usr/bin/env bash', use 'set -euo pipefail', print usage and exit non-zero if no archive is given. The archive format must match what backup.sh produces above. Output ONLY the complete contents of restore.sh inside a single ```bash code block, nothing else.
